A spokesman for the CBRC said that according to the rules of management, the relevant examination and approval method of foreign financial institutions has basically remained unchanged, that is, if a foreign bank branch is allowed to operate online banking business, it should be reviewed and reviewed by the branch's main report in China.
In June 2001, the People's Bank of China enacted the "Interim Measures on Internet banking management" to regulate the use of the Internet by commercial banks.
A spokesman for the CBRC said that with the continuous development of commercial bank electronic banking business, the interim measures cannot meet the requirements of electronic bank risk supervision, and the CBRC has formulated two new rules.
According to the spokesman of the CBRC, the CBRC's determination of a safety assessment agency qualification is different from an administrative permit based on the nature of industry access or business entry qualification. It is not a necessary condition for an evaluation agency to conduct an electronic banking safety assessment, but only as a reference for financial institutions in selecting and evaluating institutions.
As long as the safety assessment agencies comply with the relevant conditions and requirements, financial institutions may also employ them to carry out an electronic banking safety assessment, but they should be managed in accordance with the relevant regulations.
The electronic banking business management scheme consists of nine chapters and 99 articles, which are divided into nine parts, namely general principles, application and change, risk management, data exchange and transfer management, management of operations, management of cross-border operations, supervision, management, legal responsibilities and by-laws.
The "Guidelines on electronic banking safety assessment" consists of five chapters and 57 articles, which are divided into five parts, namely general principles, safety assessment bodies, implementation of safety assessment, management of safety assessment activities, and by-laws.
