The Central Organization Department called for further strengthening the supervision of the work of selecting and appointing leading cadres and cadres.
BEIJING, February 16 (Xinhua) The Organization Department of the Central Committee of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of China (CPC) recently issued a report on strengthening the supervision of cadres.
According to the opinion, the organizational departments at all levels should proceed from strict management and care for cadres, and carry out supervision of cadres in all aspects of cadre training, evaluation, selection, appointment, and day-to-day management, and effectively strengthen supervision over the selection and appointment of leading cadres and cadres.
The opinion points out that the main task of organizational cadres' supervision is to supervise leading bodies and leading cadres. The focus is on strengthening supervision of leading cadres in leading bodies; second, supervision and inspection of the work of selecting and appointing party and government leading cadres, and focusing on the implementation of the "Regulations on the selection and appointment of Party and government leading cadres."
