Cao Xiaoming rich in cultural activities in rural areas. Who is going to "pay the bill"?
Hau Wah
This year during the Spring Festival, this author was privileged to go to the mainland's countryside for the new year and visited some relatives and friends.
While they are infected with a rich new year in China's countryside, they are also worried about the boring cultural activities in the rural areas.
The author found in a village of friends and relatives that in previous years, every year during the Spring Festival, the village had to organize the villagers to play a local film called "go-round."
This film was based on the figures of three countries. The adults and children could play a role in the theater, and the villagers knew nothing about it.
In the village, there are several teams, not only in this village, but also in other villages.
However, this year the village has not been organized again.
It turns out that a big sum of money would have to be spent on getting out of the show. In the past, it was the villagers who raised money and bought them. Now, this outfit can no longer be worn.
They went from door to door and asked the villagers to offer money, and everyone was unwilling, and a similar situation occurred in several other villages in the township.
There was no "spinning signal", and the village got desolate all of a sudden.
The adults started playing mahjong.
The child also played a paper card.
The villagers all said that they had nothing to do during the past year.
Besides lighting firecrackers, playing mahjong, it has also become a big landscape for the rural new year.
On the other hand, the trend of gambling has not been stopped again and again, and there is a tendency to spread. As a result, a total of 10,000 yuan has become common. In particular, a large number of returning farmers who work in the city have become the main characters in casinos.
I earned all the hard money I earned in a year.
As a result, family disputes arising from gambling have occurred from time to time, and some have even caused the tragedy of family destruction.
Some farmers said that not only do they have gambling money for the new year, they often take part in gambling when they are idle.
If you don't gamble, then there is no place to go.
It is extremely difficult to find some cultural activities in the rural areas and to find some "joy".
There was not only a lack of facilities and funds, but there was no organization.
In this regard, Jiangxi's approach was undoubtedly a blessing for the farmers.
The Jiangxi provincial government, in order to enrich the cultural life of the peasants, has not only implemented the "government funding, market operation, market operation, and farmers' watch" since September of last year.
Each year, at least 60 million yuan of special funds for rural culture will be arranged to deliver quality cultural products to the rural people.
At the beginning of the new year, there was an additional investment of 40 million yuan, bringing in a total of 100 million yuan to set up a special fund for rural culture.
In addition, the "bills" that use this special fund to "buy" the peasants are also very beneficial:
A variety of professional arts and performance groups are invited to perform in rural areas, and not less than four in every town every year;
Film companies at all levels are invited to organize screening teams to show films in rural areas. Each administrative village does not have less than six feature films and science films per year;
It is organized to carry out mass cultural activities with local characteristics, not less than two to three times a year.
From this "purchase list", it is not difficult for us to see that the government is not trying to pay for the money. Instead, it has done a great deal of work on how to put the limited funds on the knife.
At present, the vast number of farmers are happy to enjoy the "imperial grain tax" in order to avoid handing over the "imperial grain tax."
If the government could "pay the bill" for the enrichment of the cultural activities of the peasants as it did in Jiangxi, it would be a blessing for the farmers.
This "joy" will not only enable the peasants to free themselves from the mahjong table, but also "move" in cultural activities, and also add tiles to the building of a new socialist countryside.
